A flame of flames burst forth from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a precise patch of the forest ablaze, then flew in a circle above, observing it for a time. Bizarrely, as it had slowed, the strange cries of sounds behind it had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't let myself be lifted brutally by a massive rose-colored dragon!"
"It's not that unpleasant, isn't it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi, he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws in Thassalin's back, to the point where he had made the Thraki bleed, but apparently, he didn't care much. Anyway, Thassalin had realized that he had terrorized his new friends and had found a clearing where to land.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELL SOMETHING. I SHOULD HAVE CHECKED."
"You were forced to bring us here with you?", Tenuk launched while sliding down the back of Thassalin, along her tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our great and strong fighter! How will he reach us?"
"He'll find a way", Nissy retorted. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Alright, but can Retvik drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course, he can drive."
"You have already seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I have never seen him drive something like Kayel's cute little car either, and if he started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU drive us. He just has a bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly burst into laughter and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a little too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINISCULE CHILDREN'S BIKE, CALLED TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE WANTED TO BE BORN WITH TELEPATHY. IT'S A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE! "
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's just it. But what did you gather and why did you take off so quickly?"
Thassalin groaned, took off, and disappeared briefly, before returning and dropping a carapace in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white dragon-like creature, very rare. But it was missing a head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I'M PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE CLOSE."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also did, their attention drawn by a gap in the clearing. Something big and black was staring at them, whistling. Whatever it was, this thing opened up two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, without worrying about the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to get out of the way just in time, but Nyssi was dragged and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nyssi and throwing her onto his back, using his extraordinary long and agile tail, before taking off. The black creature with two wings rushed quickly after them.
Kayel panted while drawing the gun he had on his back, then opened a pouch in which a ammunition belt was found. He put it in a holster so he could easily access it, but soon realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, want to transform into something that flies?" Kayel asked.
"You want to chase after them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And then? I have a super powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to serve. I just need to see it to shoot at it."
Tenuk hesitated, then backed off to clear a bit of space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly became the normal clear blue Thraki again, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Tenuk having regained a more normal appearance of Thraki, he now had his back covered with scales, but a pair of points had also grown on him, useful for Kayel to grab onto. Tenuk needed a bit of time to disengage, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized that they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk managed to narrowly avoid it.
I suppose it's the other big frightening monster that was worrying Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow as he tried to pull on the second beast, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on flying in the direction of Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel clumsily turned himself around to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was a bonus for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the upper wings of the creature, which screamed in pain as it disappeared again under the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it certainly wouldn't be able to catch up.
Further on, Nyssi was desperately clinging, while Thassalin flew in a circle, firing volleys of flames at the darkened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs seemed to have no effect. When Thassalin stood up, Nyssi took advantage of it to draw his gun, a reliable firearm. It wasn't of course intended for this type of situation, but a burst of shots would surely deter the black beast, wouldn't it?
